HEADWORD: Technical
<hw>Tech"nic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, fr. <?/
an art, probably from the same root as <?/, <?/, to bring forth,
produce, and perhaps akin to E. <ets>text</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>technique</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to the useful or
mechanic arts, or to any science, business, or the like; specially
appropriate to any art, science, or business; <as>as, the words of an
indictment must be <ex>technical</ex></as>.</def>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
